Citation.sAuthor: Alaoui, F. E. M.[Fatima E. M.]
Citation.sTitle: Excess Enthalpies of Binary and Ternary Mixtures Containing Dibutyl Ether, Cyclohexane, and 1-Butanol at 298.15 K
Citation.sAbstract: Experimental excess enthalpies of the ternary system dibutyl ether (DBE) + cyclohexane + 1-butanol and the corresponding binary systems at 298.15 K are reported. A quasi-isothermal flow calorimeter has been built and tested to make the measurements. All the binary and the ternary systems show endothermic character. The experimental data have been fitted using a polynomial equation for the binary and ternary systems. The values of the standard deviation indicate good agreement between the experimental results and those calculated from the equation.
